"{\"uid\": \"washingtontimes.com-news-2024-jul-31-everett-piper-reacts-to-last-supper-olympics-contr\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"OPINION: Dear Dr. E: I watched this week's Olympic ceremonies and was very disturbed by the mockery of the Last Supper.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 120, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"OPINION\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 7}, {\"ngram\": \"this week's Olympic ceremonies\", \"from\": 31, \"to\": 61}, {\"ngram\": \"the mockery\", \"from\": 88, \"to\": 99}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 103, \"to\": 118}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But nearly everyone is saying that the negative reaction from the Christian community is just another example of our intolerance.\", \"from\": 121, \"to\": 250, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 187, \"end\": 196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999911274244, \"rank\": 8.872570487598577e-09, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nearly everyone\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 140}, {\"ngram\": \"the negative reaction\", \"from\": 156, \"to\": 177}, {\"ngram\": \"just another example\", \"from\": 210, \"to\": 230}, {\"ngram\": \"our intolerance\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 249}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How do you respond to this claim?\", \"from\": 251, \"to\": 284, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this claim\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 283}]}, {\"sentence\": \"- FELLOW CHRISTIAN FROM OKLAHOMA CITY Dear Fellow Christian:A handful of years ago, I was invited to fly to Hollywood to be part of a panel to critique the premiere of the film \\\"Lord, Save Us from Your Followers.\\\"\", \"from\": 285, \"to\": 499, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 309, \"end\": 322, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_City\", \"score\": 0.9999999916290108, \"rank\": 4.87503605889628e-09, \"text\": \"OKLAHOMA CITY\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma_City\"}, {\"begin\": 394, \"end\": 403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.512902677778498e-14, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A handful\", \"from\": 345, \"to\": 354}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 358, \"to\": 363}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 409, \"to\": 413}, {\"ngram\": \"a panel\", \"from\": 417, \"to\": 424}, {\"ngram\": \"the premiere\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 449}, {\"ngram\": \"the film\", \"from\": 453, \"to\": 461}, {\"ngram\": \"Us\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 476}, {\"ngram\": \"Your Followers\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 496}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other panelists included Michael Levine, founder and president of Levine Communications, William Lobdell, former Los Angeles Times religion reporter and author of \\\"Losing My Religion,\\\" and the film's producer, Emmy award winner Dan Merchant.\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 741, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 525, \"end\": 539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_A._Levine\", \"score\": 0.999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.724529318712009e-12, \"text\": \"Michael Levine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_A._Levine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_A._Levine\"}, {\"begin\": 613, \"end\": 630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.547282489189337e-36, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Times\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Times\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Other panelists\", \"from\": 500, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"founder\", \"from\": 541, \"to\": 548}, {\"ngram\": \"president\", \"from\": 553, \"to\": 562}, {\"ngram\": \"Levine Communications\", \"from\": 566, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"William Lobdell\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 604}, {\"ngram\": \"author\", \"from\": 653, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"My Religion\", \"from\": 671, \"to\": 682}, {\"ngram\": \"the film's producer\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"Emmy award winner Dan Merchant\", \"from\": 710, \"to\": 740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I was the odd man out on the panel: a token conservative from Oklahoma to sit in juxtaposition to these other more enlightened folks of Tinseltown.\", \"from\": 742, \"to\": 889, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 804, \"end\": 812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"score\": 0.9815208323097897, \"rank\": 0.018700901637866075, \"text\": \"Oklahoma\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Oklahoma\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the odd man\", \"from\": 748, \"to\": 759}, {\"ngram\": \"the panel\", \"from\": 767, \"to\": 776}, {\"ngram\": \"a token conservative\", \"from\": 778, \"to\": 798}, {\"ngram\": \"juxtaposition\", \"from\": 823, \"to\": 836}, {\"ngram\": \"these other more enlightened folks\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 874}, {\"ngram\": \"Tinseltown\", \"from\": 878, \"to\": 888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The nature of Mr.\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 908, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The nature\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"Mr.\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 908}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Merchant's movie was simple.\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 937, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Merchant's movie\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 925}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was a \\\"man-on-the-street\\\" expos\\u00e9 portraying Christians as having an unsophisticated belief system that threatened pluralism, civil discourse, and tolerance.\", \"from\": 938, \"to\": 1097, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 985, \"end\": 995, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998298130921, \"rank\": 1.2848477409902604e-07, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the-street\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"an unsophisticated belief system\", \"from\": 1006, \"to\": 1038}, {\"ngram\": \"pluralism\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1064}, {\"ngram\": \"civil discourse\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1081}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1096}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It implied that Christians should say nothing in the public square other than, \\\"We are sorry for being so judgmental.\\\"\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1114, \"end\": 1124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998298130921, \"rank\": 1.2848477409902604e-07, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nothing\", \"from\": 1136, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"the public square\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1164}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After the movie, all of the panelists took the stage.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1271, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the movie\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1233}, {\"ngram\": \"the panelists\", \"from\": 1242, \"to\": 1255}, {\"ngram\": \"the stage\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1270}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The moderator then turned to me to answer the first question: \\\"Dr. Piper, what did you think of the movie?\\\"\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Halliwell\", \"score\": 0.9999999947121978, \"rank\": 3.4770385953662854e-09, \"text\": \"Piper\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Halliwell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Piper_Halliwell\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The moderator\", \"from\": 1272, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"the first question\", \"from\": 1314, \"to\": 1332}, {\"ngram\": \"the movie\", \"from\": 1368, \"to\": 1377}]}, {\"sentence\": \"he asked.\", \"from\": 1380, \"to\": 1389, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"My response caught him a bit off guard.\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1430, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"My response\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1402}, {\"ngram\": \"guard\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1429}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I admitted I was saddened by the thoughtless people featured in the movie, but I added that I was rather amused by the obvious indignation that served as the movie's premise.\", \"from\": 1431, \"to\": 1605, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the thoughtless people\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"the movie\", \"from\": 1495, \"to\": 1504}, {\"ngram\": \"the obvious indignation\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1569}, {\"ngram\": \"the movie's premise\", \"from\": 1585, \"to\": 1604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I then said that this negative critique of Christian behavior ironically had no meaning if there was no objective definition of righteousness to contextualize the offense.\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1778, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1650, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999911274244, \"rank\": 8.872570487598577e-09, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this negative critique\", \"from\": 1624, \"to\": 1646}, {\"ngram\": \"no meaning\", \"from\": 1684, \"to\": 1694}, {\"ngram\": \"no objective definition\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"righteousness\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1748}, {\"ngram\": \"the offense\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1777}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In other words, for the movie to mock Christians as being moralists, it had to rely on Christian morality to do so.\", \"from\": 1779, \"to\": 1894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1817, \"end\": 1827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998298130921, \"rank\": 1.2848477409902604e-07, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 1866, \"end\": 1884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_ethics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Christian morality\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_ethics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christian_ethics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other words\", \"from\": 1782, \"to\": 1793}, {\"ngram\": \"the movie\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1808}, {\"ngram\": \"moralists\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"SEE ALSO: Ask Dr. E: What do you make of young people cherry-picking religious beliefs for political purposes?\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 2006, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Dr. E\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1915}, {\"ngram\": \"young people\", \"from\": 1937, \"to\": 1949}, {\"ngram\": \"religious beliefs\", \"from\": 1965, \"to\": 1982}, {\"ngram\": \"political purposes\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2005}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Think about it.\", \"from\": 2008, \"to\": 2023, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Because Christianity is grounded in an immutable standard of right and wrong, it is Christianity itself that provides the standard that its critics use to criticize it.\", \"from\": 2024, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2032, \"end\": 2044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999995415692, \"rank\": 4.584099303493932e-09, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2108, \"end\": 2120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999995415692, \"rank\": 4.584099303493932e-09, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an immutable standard\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"right\", \"from\": 2085, \"to\": 2090}, {\"ngram\": \"wrong\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2100}, {\"ngram\": \"the standard\", \"from\": 2142, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"its critics\", \"from\": 2160, \"to\": 2171}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In other words, without Christian orthodoxy (right ideas), the heterodox cannot mock orthodox Christians for lacking orthopraxy (right behavior).\", \"from\": 2193, \"to\": 2338, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2217, \"end\": 2226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999911274244, \"rank\": 8.872570487598577e-09, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 2278, \"end\": 2297, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orthodoxy\", \"score\": 0.9999999976612344, \"rank\": 2.158149926122044e-09, \"text\": \"orthodox Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orthodoxy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orthodoxy\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other words\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2207}, {\"ngram\": \"(right ideas\", \"from\": 2237, \"to\": 2249}, {\"ngram\": \"the heterodox\", \"from\": 2252, \"to\": 2265}, {\"ngram\": \"orthopraxy\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2320}, {\"ngram\": \"right behavior\", \"from\": 2322, \"to\": 2336}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another way of saying it is that accusing someone of intolerance is rather silly unless you have some objective definition of what you find intolerable.\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2491, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Another way\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2350}, {\"ngram\": \"someone\", \"from\": 2381, \"to\": 2388}, {\"ngram\": \"intolerance\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2403}, {\"ngram\": \"some objective definition\", \"from\": 2436, \"to\": 2461}]}, {\"sentence\": \"C. S. Lewis explained this in \\\"The Poison of Subjectivism.\\\"\", \"from\": 2493, \"to\": 2552, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2499, \"end\": 2504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meldrick_Lewis\", \"score\": 0.9993835103285533, \"rank\": 0.0006167856303605236, \"text\": \"Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meldrick_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meldrick_Lewis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Poison\", \"from\": 2524, \"to\": 2534}, {\"ngram\": \"Subjectivism\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2550}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's a brief excerpt of his remarks: \\\"Until modern times, no thinker of the first rank ever doubted that our judgments of value were rational\\u2026 or that what they discovered was objective.\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2741, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a brief excerpt\", \"from\": 2560, \"to\": 2575}, {\"ngram\": \"his remarks\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2590}, {\"ngram\": \"modern times\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2611}, {\"ngram\": \"no thinker\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2623}, {\"ngram\": \"the first rank\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2641}, {\"ngram\": \"our judgments\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2673}, {\"ngram\": \"value\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was taken for granted that in temptation, passion was opposed, not to some sentiment, but to reason.\\\"\", \"from\": 2742, \"to\": 2846, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"temptation\", \"from\": 2775, \"to\": 2785}, {\"ngram\": \"passion\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 2794}, {\"ngram\": \"some sentiment\", \"from\": 2815, \"to\": 2829}, {\"ngram\": \"reason\", \"from\": 2838, \"to\": 2844}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He went on: \\\"The modern view is very different.\", \"from\": 2848, \"to\": 2895, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The modern view\", \"from\": 2861, \"to\": 2876}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It does not believe that value judgments are really judgments at all.\", \"from\": 2896, \"to\": 2965, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"value judgments\", \"from\": 2921, \"to\": 2936}, {\"ngram\": \"judgments\", \"from\": 2948, \"to\": 2957}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are sentiments\\u2026 To say that a thing is good is merely to express our feelings about it\\u2026 But if this is so, then we might have been conditioned to feel otherwise.\", \"from\": 2966, \"to\": 3132, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sentiments\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 2985}, {\"ngram\": \"a thing\", \"from\": 2999, \"to\": 3006}, {\"ngram\": \"our feelings\", \"from\": 3036, \"to\": 3048}]}, {\"sentence\": \"'Perhaps,' thinks the reformer or the educational expert, 'it would be better if we were.\", \"from\": 3133, \"to\": 3222, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the reformer\", \"from\": 3151, \"to\": 3163}, {\"ngram\": \"the educational expert\", \"from\": 3167, \"to\": 3189}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Let us improve our morality.'\\\"\", \"from\": 3223, \"to\": 3253, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 3227, \"to\": 3229}, {\"ngram\": \"our morality\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3250}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Out of this apparently innocent idea,\\\" concludes Lewis, \\\"comes the disease that will certainly end our species if it is not crushed; the fatal superstition that men can create values and that a community can choose its ideology as men choose their clothes.\\\"\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3513, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3305, \"end\": 3310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meldrick_Lewis\", \"score\": 0.9993835103285533, \"rank\": 0.0006167856303605236, \"text\": \"Lewis\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meldrick_Lewis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Meldrick_Lewis\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this apparently innocent idea\", \"from\": 3263, \"to\": 3292}, {\"ngram\": \"the disease\", \"from\": 3319, \"to\": 3330}, {\"ngram\": \"our species\", \"from\": 3355, \"to\": 3366}, {\"ngram\": \"the fatal superstition\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3411}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 3417, \"to\": 3420}, {\"ngram\": \"values\", \"from\": 3432, \"to\": 3438}, {\"ngram\": \"a community\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3459}, {\"ngram\": \"its ideology\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3483}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 3487, \"to\": 3490}, {\"ngram\": \"their clothes\", \"from\": 3498, \"to\": 3511}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The \\\"tolerance\\\" celebrated at the Olympics is indeed that \\\"fatal superstition.\\\"\", \"from\": 3515, \"to\": 3594, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The \\\"tolerance\", \"from\": 3515, \"to\": 3529}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3545, \"to\": 3557}, {\"ngram\": \"that \\\"fatal superstition\", \"from\": 3568, \"to\": 3592}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If this is not the poster child of \\\"choosing our values as men choose their clothes,\\\" I do not know what is.\", \"from\": 3595, \"to\": 3703, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the poster child\", \"from\": 3610, \"to\": 3626}, {\"ngram\": \"our values\", \"from\": 3640, \"to\": 3650}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 3654, \"to\": 3657}, {\"ngram\": \"their clothes\", \"from\": 3665, \"to\": 3678}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But any schoolboy can see the hypocrisy in it all.\", \"from\": 3704, \"to\": 3754, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any schoolboy\", \"from\": 3708, \"to\": 3721}, {\"ngram\": \"the hypocrisy\", \"from\": 3730, \"to\": 3743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"None of this is really about tolerance, and it never has been.\", \"from\": 3755, \"to\": 3817, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"None\", \"from\": 3755, \"to\": 3759}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 3784, \"to\": 3793}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the contrary, the self-styled advocates of \\\"openness and peace\\\" are clearly more interested in tyranny and power.\", \"from\": 3818, \"to\": 3934, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the contrary\", \"from\": 3821, \"to\": 3833}, {\"ngram\": \"the self-styled advocates\", \"from\": 3835, \"to\": 3860}, {\"ngram\": \"openness\", \"from\": 3865, \"to\": 3873}, {\"ngram\": \"peace\", \"from\": 3878, \"to\": 3883}, {\"ngram\": \"tyranny\", \"from\": 3916, \"to\": 3923}, {\"ngram\": \"power\", \"from\": 3928, \"to\": 3933}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At every turn, whether it be in Dan Merchant's movie or on the present-day streets of Paris, we see them with their angry red faces as they shout, \\\"You must agree with us!\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 4106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4021, \"end\": 4026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999653887249, \"rank\": 3.461135360700789e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every turn\", \"from\": 3938, \"to\": 3948}, {\"ngram\": \"Dan Merchant's movie\", \"from\": 3967, \"to\": 3987}, {\"ngram\": \"the present-day streets\", \"from\": 3994, \"to\": 4017}, {\"ngram\": \"their angry red faces\", \"from\": 4045, \"to\": 4066}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 4103, \"to\": 4105}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You must celebrate everything we do!\", \"from\": 4107, \"to\": 4143, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 4126, \"to\": 4136}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You must watch, and you must applaud!\\\"\", \"from\": 4144, \"to\": 4182, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tolerating anything they find intolerable is of no interest to them.\", \"from\": 4183, \"to\": 4251, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anything\", \"from\": 4194, \"to\": 4202}, {\"ngram\": \"no interest\", \"from\": 4231, \"to\": 4242}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The end goal of the worldview that was on full display in the opening ceremonies of the Olympics is not tolerance or freedom but ideological fascism, pure and simple.\", \"from\": 4253, \"to\": 4419, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The end goal\", \"from\": 4253, \"to\": 4265}, {\"ngram\": \"the worldview\", \"from\": 4269, \"to\": 4282}, {\"ngram\": \"full display\", \"from\": 4295, \"to\": 4307}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremonies\", \"from\": 4311, \"to\": 4333}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4337, \"to\": 4349}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 4357, \"to\": 4366}, {\"ngram\": \"freedom\", \"from\": 4370, \"to\": 4377}, {\"ngram\": \"ideological fascism\", \"from\": 4382, \"to\": 4401}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's the intolerance being pushed by these champions of tolerance.\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the intolerance\", \"from\": 4427, \"to\": 4442}, {\"ngram\": \"these champions\", \"from\": 4459, \"to\": 4474}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 4478, \"to\": 4487}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That's the conformity they have in mind when they criticize Christians for being conformists.\", \"from\": 4489, \"to\": 4582, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4549, \"end\": 4559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998298130921, \"rank\": 1.2848477409902604e-07, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [